we have realease deployment and the deployment is successfull and changes are not reflectign ?but cicd pipeline is showing successfull deployed ?

This is a very common real-world DevOps/SRE scenario — and interviewers love this one.

If deployment is successful in CI/CD but changes are NOT reflecting, it usually means the issue is after deployment, not in the pipeline.

Let’s break it down like an L2 engineer 👇

🔍 Possible Causes & How to Check
1. 🚫 Old Pods Still Running (No rollout happened)
Deployment succeeded but pods didn’t restart

Happens if image tag is same (like latest)

✅ Check:

kubectl get pods
kubectl describe deployment <app>
👉 Fix:

kubectl rollout restart deployment <app>
2. 🐳 Same Docker Image Tag Used
CI/CD says success, but Kubernetes pulls cached image

Common mistake: using latest tag

✅ Check:

kubectl describe pod <pod-name> | grep Image
👉 Fix:

Use unique tags (build number / commit ID)

Or set:

imagePullPolicy: Always
3. 🌐 Browser / CDN Cache Issue
App updated but browser still shows old content

✅ Check:

Open in incognito

Hard refresh (Ctrl + Shift + R)

👉 Fix:

Clear cache / invalidate CDN

4. ⚖️ Load Balancer Routing to Old Version
Traffic still hitting old pods

✅ Check:

kubectl get svc
kubectl get endpoints
👉 Fix:

Ensure new pods are ready

Check readiness/liveness probes

5. ❌ Wrong Environment / Namespace
Deployed to dev, checking in prod

✅ Check:

kubectl config current-context
kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
6. ⚙️ ConfigMap / Secret Not Updated
Code depends on config but config didn’t change

👉 Fix:

kubectl rollout restart deployment <app>
7. 🚫 Build Issue (Artifact not updated)
Pipeline succeeded but old code packaged

✅ Check:

Verify build logs

Check image version pushed

8. 🔁 Ingress / API Gateway Cache
Ingress caching old responses

👉 Fix:

Restart ingress controller

Clear cache (if enabled)

🧠 How to Answer in Interview (2–3 lines)
👉 Best Answer:

Even if CI/CD shows successful deployment, changes may not reflect due to cached Docker images, unchanged image tags, or pods not restarting. I would verify pod rollout, check image version, and ensure correct namespace and cache invalidation.

